    fix(auth): replace module-level isLoggingIn flag with React state
    
    The isLoggingIn flag was a plain module-level variable (let isLoggingIn = false).
    When login() resolved and set isLoggingIn = false in the finally block,
    React had no way to know — so ProtectedRoute/GuestRoute never re-rendered
    after the login completed. This caused the /mangaka route to stay blocked at
    'Loading...' forever after successful navigation.
    
    Fix: move isLoggingIn into AuthProvider's useState, expose it via context
    as loggingIn, and have ProtectedRoute/GuestRoute/HomeOrWorkspace read it
    from useAuth() so they re-render when it flips true→false.
    
    Also added [component] prefix tags to all console.log calls for easier
    filtering in browser DevTools.
    
    Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>

