    fix(Mangaka): resolve TDZ on apiSeries in /mangaka route
    
    The useMemo for annotateSeriesId accessed piSeries in its dependency
    array before the piSeries const was declared at line 437. React's
    dependency array is evaluated during component function execution,
    triggering a Temporal Dead Zone ReferenceError on mount:
    
      ReferenceError: Cannot access 'apiSeries' before initialization
    
    This crashed <Mangaka> immediately after navigation, causing
    ErrorBoundary to render <Route path='*'> which navigated back to '/'.
    
    Move the annotateSeriesId useMemo and the related useChapters call
    below the declaration of apiSeries so the dependency is in scope.
    
