    fix(auth): resolve snake_case + PascalCase fields from login response
    
    axiosClient.js is normalizing PascalCase response keys to snake_case
    (userId -> user_id, roleId -> role_id, refreshToken -> refresh_token, ...).
    buildSessionFromAuthResponse only checked PascalCase variants, so on a
    real backend response it resolved id, userid, name, fullname, roleid,
    refreshToken to null/undefined. That left localStorage.refreshToken as
    the string "undefined", which then broke the next API call with a 401.
    
    Replace the ad-hoc chain with a pick(obj, keys) helper that accepts both
    snake_case and PascalCase for every field, so the session resolves
    correctly regardless of whether the backend returns PascalCase (which
    gets normalized) or snake_case directly.
    
    Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>

